awareness among students. The department focuses on building confidence in reading, writing, speaking, and comprehension, which are essential for higher education, employment, and personal growth. Through a balanced approach to language and literature, the department helps students appreciate the richness of English studies while also preparing them for practical communication in academic and professional environments. Vision To create a vibrant academic environment that promotes language competence, literary sensibility, critical thinking, and effective communication for lifelong learning and global engagement. Mission To strengthen students’ communication skills in English for academic and professional success. To cultivate interest in literature, language, and culture through meaningful learning experiences. To develop critical, analytical, and creative thinking abilities among students. To prepare learners for competitive examinations, interviews, and career opportunities. To encourage confidence, personality development, and ethical values through language education. Programs and Courses Compulsory English for undergraduate students. Optional English courses for students interested in advanced study of language and literature. Foundation and communication skill courses. Certificate courses in Spoken English, Business Communication, and Creative Writing. Bridge and remedial courses for students requiring additional support in language learning. Key Activities Language laboratory sessions for pronunciation and speaking practice. Debate, elocution, essay writing, and poetry recitation competitions. Creative writing workshops and book review presentations. Seminars, guest lectures, and personality development sessions. Communication skill enhancement activities for placements and interviews. Faculty Expertise English Language Teaching (ELT) British Literature Indian Writing in English American Literature Literary Criticism Communicative English and Soft Skills Learning Outcomes Students communicate effectively in academic and workplace settings. Students gain confidence in public speaking, presentation, and writing skills. Students develop the ability to read and interpret literary texts critically. Students improve their grammar, vocabulary, and overall language competence. Students become better prepared for interviews, competitive exams, and career advancement. Department Features Student-centered teaching and interactive classroom practices. Access to library resources, literary texts, and reference materials. Focus on communication training and employability skills. Encouragement for participation in literary and cultural activities. Faculty Profile Video --> Courses Speakers --> Gallery --> Research Scholar Activities --> Sr. No. Name of the Staff Designation Qualification Subject Taught Experience Photo Contact No. E-mail 1 Mr. Vikas Madhav Basvante Assist. Prof., HoD M.A(Eng.), M.Phil, SET(Eng.) 01) Grammar & Composition-II 02) Developing Written Commu. 6 9890712741 vikasbasvante93@gmail.com 2 Dr. Shiveshwar M. Muchate Assistant Professor M.A(Eng.), Ph.D, SET(Eng.) 01) Developing Written Commu. 02) English For Comp. Exam-I & II 10 7387542773 smmuchate123@gmail.com 3 Ms. Arti Bajiro Patil Assistant Professor M.A(Eng.), SET(Eng.) 01) General English 02) Developing Written Commu. 4 7743909571 4 Mr. Pawan Shankar Wadje Assistant Professor M.A(Eng.) 01) English For Comp. Exam-I & II 02) Developing Spoken Commu. 2 9970777073 pawan.wadje@gmail.com 5 Ms. Bhgyashree G. Suryawanshi Assistant Professor M.A(Eng.), M.Phil, SET, NET 01) English For Comp. Exam-I & II 02) Developing Spoken Commu. 2 Photo 6 Dr. Sandeep Sambhaji Dhore Assistant Professor M.A(Eng.), SET, NET, Ph.D. 01) Grammar & Composition-II 02) Developing Written Commu. 06 7 Dr. T. Guru Sowmya Lakkoju Assistant Professor M.A(Eng.), Ph.D. 01) General English 02) Developing Written Commu. 06 Photo SN Name of the Course Eligibility Duration 01 BCA 12 th - Any Faculty 3/